        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 8 at 1:20PM CDT by NWS Lincoln IL</headline>
        <description>At 119 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Paris, moving southwest at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor hail damage to vegetation is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Paris, Vermilion, Edgar County Airport, Isabel, Redmon, Sandford, and
Borton.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
